Here's the chief of the National Police Agency.

4
00:00:09,390 --> 00:00:10,860
The police...

5
00:00:10,860 --> 00:00:13,100
protect the citizens...

6
00:00:13,100 --> 00:00:14,700
of the underclass.

7
00:00:14,700 --> 00:00:18,330
They promote justice and advocate for the people.

8
00:00:18,330 --> 00:00:22,870
You're the future of the police.

9
00:00:22,870 --> 00:00:25,240
Please do not forget...

10
00:00:25,240 --> 00:00:29,720
the citizens' expectations of you.

11
00:00:29,720 --> 00:00:32,890
Look after this country and its people.

12
00:00:32,890 --> 00:00:36,450
Always be reliable and honorable.

13
00:00:36,450 --> 00:00:39,420
Please safeguard your reputation.

14
00:00:39,420 --> 00:00:41,930
Salute to the chief of National Police Agency.

15
00:00:41,930 --> 00:00:44,120
- Salute.
- Salute.

16
00:00:45,260 --> 00:00:47,260
Salute.

17
00:00:50,540 --> 00:00:51,870
At ease.

18
00:00:51,870 --> 00:00:53,500
I take this oath.

19
00:00:53,500 --> 00:00:54,580
- I take this oath.
- I take this oath.

20
00:00:54,580 --> 00:00:56,840
"I abide by the constitution and the law."

21
00:00:56,840 --> 00:00:58,400
"I respect the rights."

22
00:00:58,400 --> 00:01:00,570
"I take this oath sincerely."

23
00:01:00,570 --> 00:01:03,850
Graduating Police Officer Chae Dojin.

24
00:01:03,850 --> 00:01:07,810
Here's the award presentation for those with top grades.

25
00:01:07,810 --> 00:01:09,060
Presidential Award.

26
00:01:09,060 --> 00:01:12,090
Police Officer Chae Dojin.

27
00:01:12,090 --> 00:01:14,800
Please step forward.

28
00:01:21,200 --> 00:01:22,940
[Police University Class of 31st Year]

29
00:01:22,940 --> 00:01:25,230
Salute.

30
00:01:45,590 --> 00:01:47,230
Salute.

31
00:01:47,230 --> 00:01:48,950
[Nation, Justice, Honor]

32
00:01:57,940 --> 00:02:00,440
- You're a fake.
- What's happening?

33
00:02:00,440 --> 00:02:02,940
You spouted lies on television!

34
00:02:02,940 --> 00:02:05,270
[Withdraw His Presidential Award]

35
00:02:05,270 --> 00:02:07,840
- His dad is a killer.
- How dare you?

36
00:02:07,840 --> 00:02:09,980
- Hey.
- Who do you think you are?

37
00:02:09,980 --> 00:02:11,710
How dare you?

38
00:02:11,710 --> 00:02:13,320
You don't deserve this.

39
00:02:13,320 --> 00:02:14,390
[Don't kill us twice]

40
00:02:14,390 --> 00:02:15,450
[Yoon Huijae's autography must be destroyed]

41
00:02:15,450 --> 00:02:16,450
- Move.
- Move out of the way.

42
00:02:16,450 --> 00:02:18,230
- He's a murderer.
- Stop.

43
00:02:18,230 --> 00:02:20,760
- You hypocrite.
- You're a killer.

44
00:02:20,760 --> 00:02:22,100
You can't be a police officer.

45
00:02:22,100 --> 00:02:23,960
You call yourself the police?

46
00:02:23,960 --> 00:02:25,520
You're not the police.

47
00:02:25,520 --> 00:02:27,640
- You punk.
- Move out of the way.

48
00:02:27,640 --> 00:02:28,670
Please!

49
00:02:28,670 --> 00:02:31,510
- He's Yoon Huijae's son.
- Take it easy, please.

50
00:02:31,510 --> 00:02:34,200
He killed my mother!

51
00:02:34,200 --> 00:02:37,270
- He's a killer.
- How unfair for you.

52
00:02:37,270 --> 00:02:40,380
- He's a killer.
- He can't be the police.

53
00:02:40,380 --> 00:02:42,640
He's from a trash family.

54
00:02:42,640 --> 00:02:45,450
Mr. President, this is unjust!

55
00:02:45,450 --> 00:02:48,510
I can't believe this!

56
00:02:48,510 --> 00:02:52,120
- Release me, sheesh.
- Make them live once again.

57
00:02:52,120 --> 00:02:54,500
Please let those people go.

58
00:03:01,530 --> 00:03:03,670
It's okay.

59
00:03:03,670 --> 00:03:05,630
Please let go of them.

60
00:03:12,550 --> 00:03:13,740
You punk.

61
00:03:13,740 --> 00:03:17,210
Like father like son, you and your father are so brazen.

62
00:03:17,210 --> 00:03:21,890
You knew that he would be doing that.

63
00:03:21,890 --> 00:03:25,390
Who gave you the right to produce such a TV show?

64
00:03:25,390 --> 00:03:28,300
Did your father tell you to do that?

65
00:03:28,300 --> 00:03:31,620
Young man, lay your eyes on this.

66
00:03:31,620 --> 00:03:33,500
Is this real?

67
00:03:35,830 --> 00:03:38,930
You were putting on a show on TV, right?

68
00:03:38,930 --> 00:03:42,600
You finished your studies at the top of your class? A lieutenant?

69
00:03:45,670 --> 00:03:47,740
If his son is so precious,

70
00:03:47,740 --> 00:03:50,290
how was he unaware of how much I cherish my son?

71
00:03:50,290 --> 00:03:53,240
Why would he not know? Why not?

72
00:03:54,360 --> 00:03:57,620
Take your dirty hands off of her!

73
00:04:10,300 --> 00:04:11,360
[The killer reaps profits from his autobiography]

74
00:04:24,810 --> 00:04:26,620
I apologize.

75
00:04:29,890 --> 00:04:31,520
I really...

76
00:04:33,290 --> 00:04:34,600
am very sorry.

77
00:04:34,600 --> 00:04:36,460
[Withdraw His Presidential Award]

78
00:04:51,870 --> 00:04:54,920
Stop this, you punk!

79
00:04:55,980 --> 00:04:57,850
Why you...

80
00:05:12,220 --> 00:05:15,230
What about my mom?

81
00:05:15,990 --> 00:05:17,970
What about my mom?

82
00:05:17,970 --> 00:05:19,710
- Hey!
- Sir.

83
00:05:19,710 --> 00:05:21,130
- You punk.
- Hold him.

84
00:05:21,130 --> 00:05:23,710
- Hold him.
- You punk.

85
00:05:23,710 --> 00:05:26,150
- Stop, sir.
- Let me go.

86
00:05:26,150 --> 00:05:28,720
Let me go!

87
00:05:28,720 --> 00:05:30,720
You punk, what about my mom?

88
00:05:30,720 --> 00:05:32,520
- Please, sir.
- Let me go.

89
00:05:32,520 --> 00:05:34,420
Let go of me!

90
00:05:34,420 --> 00:05:37,380
Hey, be honest with me.

91
00:05:37,380 --> 00:05:41,160
Come here, you. And my mother?

92
00:05:41,160 --> 00:05:43,870
Be honest.

93
00:05:43,870 --> 00:05:47,320
- You're not sorry.
- Namu.

94
00:05:47,320 --> 00:05:51,810
I can see you have no remorse toward my mother.

95
00:05:53,170 --> 00:05:54,710
Nakwon,

96
00:05:55,670 --> 00:05:59,300
do you know why my mother named me Namu?

97
00:05:59,300 --> 00:06:01,170
Have I told you?

98
00:06:03,850 --> 00:06:05,180
Of course.

99
00:06:05,180 --> 00:06:08,950
The story touched me very much.

100
00:06:10,180 --> 00:06:12,120
It's you...

101
00:06:12,120 --> 00:06:14,760
who makes me resemble a tree.

102
00:06:14,760 --> 00:06:16,700
Did I tell you that too?

103
00:06:20,900 --> 00:06:24,010
Just like the name my mother chose for me.

104
00:06:24,010 --> 00:06:26,160
Like an actual tree.

105
00:06:26,840 --> 00:06:29,410
Without doing anything bad,

106
00:06:29,410 --> 00:06:31,940
I'll get through life...

107
00:06:32,940 --> 00:06:35,270
and become an adult.

108
00:06:38,550 --> 00:06:40,140
It's you...

109
00:06:41,090 --> 00:06:43,350
who made me that way.

110
00:07:25,270 --> 00:07:27,360
Hey, you!

111
00:07:27,360 --> 00:07:29,430
Tell us. Get those hands off.

112
00:07:29,430 --> 00:07:33,040
- Are you really sorry?
- That's enough.

113
00:07:33,040 --> 00:07:34,800
Do you really feel bad?

114
00:07:34,800 --> 00:07:36,210
My mom.

115
00:07:36,210 --> 00:07:38,400
What are you doing?

116
00:07:38,410 --> 00:07:40,550
What did my baby do to deserve this?

117
00:07:40,550 --> 00:07:43,220
Are you all right? What's going on?

118
00:07:43,220 --> 00:07:47,650
How is my mom at fault?

119
00:07:47,650 --> 00:07:50,480
What about the families here?

120
00:07:50,480 --> 00:07:54,490
Just what did we do to deserve this?

121
00:07:54,490 --> 00:07:58,190
How could he commit such acts?

122
00:07:58,190 --> 00:07:59,770
That man...

123
00:07:59,770 --> 00:08:03,030
deserves to be stabbed and killed.

124
00:08:03,030 --> 00:08:06,110
But not my baby.

125
00:08:06,110 --> 00:08:09,870
He tried to put a stop to the publication of his dad's autobiography.

126
00:08:09,870 --> 00:08:12,570
That's why he went on TV.

127
00:08:14,320 --> 00:08:16,450
He's trying

128
00:08:16,450 --> 00:08:19,250
to pursue a different path from his dad.

129
00:08:29,660 --> 00:08:31,500
Honey.

130
00:08:33,230 --> 00:08:35,430
Woonmyeong.

131
00:08:35,430 --> 00:08:38,800
I'm sorry.

132
00:08:38,800 --> 00:08:43,040
Your mom is only to blame.

133
00:08:43,040 --> 00:08:47,450
I'm so sorry. Your mother is sorry.

134
00:08:49,470 --> 00:08:52,150
It's all my fault.

135
00:08:52,150 --> 00:08:55,220
It's your mom's fault.

136
00:08:56,620 --> 00:08:59,720
Could you take care of...

137
00:08:59,720 --> 00:09:01,390
my mother and Sohjin separately?

138
00:09:01,400 --> 00:09:03,390
I will.

139
00:09:04,170 --> 00:09:05,670
Mother.

140
00:09:05,670 --> 00:09:07,870
Let's get away from here.

141
00:09:07,870 --> 00:09:10,000
Too many reporters are here.

142
00:09:11,370 --> 00:09:13,060
[Parent of graduate]

143
00:09:59,250 --> 00:10:00,710
[My daughter had a dream just like you]

144
00:10:51,700 --> 00:10:53,430
Namu.

145
00:11:13,260 --> 00:11:15,120
She's the one...

146
00:11:15,920 --> 00:11:18,500
that my father...

147
00:11:19,300 --> 00:11:21,170
stole everything from.

148
00:11:27,570 --> 00:11:30,270
I must ask for forgiveness for the remainder of my days

149
00:11:30,270 --> 00:11:32,950
for something I didn't do.

150
00:11:36,620 --> 00:11:38,980
I must flee until I die

151
00:11:39,810 --> 00:11:42,460
for something I didn't do.

152
00:11:44,080 --> 00:11:45,460
My only...

153
00:11:47,030 --> 00:11:48,830
paradise.

154
00:11:54,640 --> 00:11:57,600
I told you to say something if you feel pain.

155
00:12:01,040 --> 00:12:03,710
I said not to take on burdens alone.

156
00:12:11,150 --> 00:12:12,820
Tell me.

157
00:12:19,820 --> 00:12:21,500
Namu.

158
00:12:28,660 --> 00:12:30,390
Tell me.

159
00:13:13,400 --> 00:13:14,920
Who the hell are you?

160
00:13:18,310 --> 00:13:21,220
I'll buy this from you.

161
00:13:41,570 --> 00:13:43,770
Don't touch my younger sister.

162
00:13:46,280 --> 00:13:48,020
Muwon.

163
00:13:57,130 --> 00:13:58,950
I didn't want to say

164
00:13:58,950 --> 00:14:01,220
it's been a while,

165
00:14:01,220 --> 00:14:03,500
but it has been a while.

166
00:14:03,500 --> 00:14:05,490
It's been about nine years?

167
00:14:05,490 --> 00:14:07,870
Didn't I tell you back then, too?

168
00:14:07,870 --> 00:14:10,740
I warned you not to show your face to my family again.

169
00:14:25,420 --> 00:14:26,950
[Chae Dojin]

170
00:14:30,130 --> 00:14:31,980
I don't care who you are now...

171
00:14:31,980 --> 00:14:34,590
or what kind of mask you're wearing.

172
00:14:34,590 --> 00:14:36,730
Don't forget...

173
00:14:37,730 --> 00:14:39,570
the warning I gave you,

174
00:14:39,570 --> 00:14:41,590
Yoon Namu.

175
00:14:46,800 --> 00:14:48,480
Let's go.

176
00:15:12,320 --> 00:15:14,100
Nakwon.

177
00:15:30,520 --> 00:15:32,020
Let's go.

178
00:16:16,790 --> 00:16:18,370
Unnie,

179
00:16:20,500 --> 00:16:22,500
are you all right?

180
00:16:27,430 --> 00:16:30,510
I don't think you can bear it, unlike the rest of us.

181
00:16:30,510 --> 00:16:32,850
Don't try too hard.

182
00:16:34,410 --> 00:16:35,940
Here.

183
00:16:38,540 --> 00:16:41,120
Can you just hold onto this?

184
00:16:45,730 --> 00:16:47,760
If it hurts you too much,

185
00:16:47,760 --> 00:16:49,930
you can discard it.

186
00:17:20,530 --> 00:17:21,960
[2006.12.24, Gil]

187
00:17:26,460 --> 00:17:28,290
Mom...

188
00:17:28,290 --> 00:17:33,240
[2006.12.24, Jee]

189
00:17:44,290 --> 00:17:45,750
[I'm sorry, Mom]

190
00:18:00,200 --> 00:18:02,060
[2006.12.24, Jee]

191
00:18:15,640 --> 00:18:17,490
[2006.12.24, Jee]

192
00:18:34,730 --> 00:18:36,370
Nakwon.

193
00:18:52,520 --> 00:18:54,090
It's all right.

194
00:18:55,650 --> 00:18:57,790
We can get through this...

195
00:18:59,260 --> 00:19:01,130
again.

196
00:19:13,160 --> 00:19:15,430
You must have had it hard today.

197
00:19:15,430 --> 00:19:17,770
Congratulations on the graduation.

198
00:19:17,770 --> 00:19:21,910
You're good at coping no matter, what's going on.

199
00:19:21,910 --> 00:19:25,650
It's not for nothing that dads tend to favor their youngest children.

200
00:19:25,650 --> 00:19:27,180
Just stop it.

201
00:19:27,180 --> 00:19:29,950
Your dad really wants to see you.

202
00:19:29,950 --> 00:19:31,490
Why don't you come with me soon?

203
00:19:31,490 --> 00:19:33,260
Was that...

204
00:19:34,250 --> 00:19:36,700
the only deal you got?

205
00:19:37,490 --> 00:19:39,670
Well, there was that too.

206
00:19:41,100 --> 00:19:42,200
But I thought...

207
00:19:42,200 --> 00:19:44,810
there was a secret that only the two of you are privy to.

208
00:19:44,810 --> 00:19:47,030
What that is...

209
00:19:47,030 --> 00:19:49,730
would change what the price will be.

210
00:19:52,050 --> 00:19:54,770
The person who helped Gil Nakwon here...

211
00:19:54,770 --> 00:19:56,310
wasn't that you?

212
00:19:56,980 --> 00:20:00,680
The person Gil Muwon dragged away was Nakwon.

213
00:20:01,590 --> 00:20:03,420
What are you two?

214
00:20:03,420 --> 00:20:05,820
Do you two...

215
00:20:05,820 --> 00:20:08,060
still like each other?

216
00:20:11,660 --> 00:20:13,570
That's nonsense.

217
00:20:13,570 --> 00:20:15,240
You know,

218
00:20:15,970 --> 00:20:18,670
she's really rude.

219
00:20:23,880 --> 00:20:27,200
I said not to lay your hands on her.

220
00:20:28,210 --> 00:20:30,850
Nine years ago and even now,

221
00:20:30,850 --> 00:20:32,690
I told you not to...

222
00:20:32,690 --> 00:20:35,350
- touch her or...
- You're...

223
00:20:35,350 --> 00:20:38,230
partially responsible for what happened to her.

224
00:20:41,560 --> 00:20:43,790
Your dad is subhuman.

225
00:20:43,790 --> 00:20:48,170
You chose to be with her, despite knowing your dad was a monster.

226
00:20:48,170 --> 00:20:50,230
That's on you.

227
00:20:51,200 --> 00:20:53,460
You must know that.

228
00:20:55,670 --> 00:20:58,600
You have no conscience like son, like father.

229
00:21:32,650 --> 00:21:34,670
I'm okay.

230
00:21:34,670 --> 00:21:36,920
I'm okay, too.

231
00:21:36,920 --> 00:21:39,710
You can't be okay.

232
00:21:39,710 --> 00:21:42,290
Your face looks terrible.

233
00:21:42,290 --> 00:21:46,160
Early tomorrow morning, you're leaving, so why are you here?

234
00:21:46,860 --> 00:21:48,690
We had to...

235
00:21:48,690 --> 00:21:51,330
hurry and pack.

236
00:21:51,330 --> 00:21:55,170
That's why we were late.

237
00:21:55,170 --> 00:21:57,600
I'm sorry, my son.

238
00:22:02,780 --> 00:22:06,670
We'll meet much more frequently when you reside in Seoul.

239
00:22:07,380 --> 00:22:09,750
I'm sorry I can't...

240
00:22:09,750 --> 00:22:11,620
help you move.

241
00:22:13,710 --> 00:22:15,590
Dojin.

242
00:22:15,590 --> 00:22:17,160
Yes?

243
00:22:18,790 --> 00:22:20,590
When you want to cry,

244
00:22:20,590 --> 00:22:23,130
don't stop yourself. Just cry.

245
00:22:24,490 --> 00:22:26,430
When you're sad, cry.

246
00:22:26,430 --> 00:22:28,590
When you're tired, hug.

247
00:22:28,590 --> 00:22:30,970
That's how we live.

248
00:22:34,640 --> 00:22:36,670
Holding back...

249
00:22:38,680 --> 00:22:41,110
comes later.

250
00:22:41,110 --> 00:22:44,220
When you've given it your all

251
00:22:44,220 --> 00:22:46,990
and yielded no results,

252
00:22:46,990 --> 00:22:49,380
that's when you can hold back.

253
00:22:57,460 --> 00:22:59,360
Thank you.

254
00:23:00,660 --> 00:23:02,700
It was a harsh storm,

255
00:23:02,700 --> 00:23:05,870
but you survived it intact.

256
00:23:05,870 --> 00:23:09,440
As a mom, I'm very...

257
00:23:09,440 --> 00:23:11,970
proud of you.

258
00:23:12,950 --> 00:23:16,520
Others' words are insignificant...

259
00:23:16,520 --> 00:23:20,080
my son is the best to me.

260
00:23:22,590 --> 00:23:24,250
Do you know...

261
00:23:24,250 --> 00:23:26,030
how I feel, right?

262
00:23:35,600 --> 00:23:37,610
I'm hungry.

263
00:23:37,610 --> 00:23:40,840
- Let's go eat.
- My sweet, little piggy.

264
00:23:40,840 --> 00:23:43,000
I was wondering where you were.

265
00:23:43,000 --> 00:23:45,310
I'll catch up with you.

266
00:23:46,110 --> 00:23:49,510
Take your time.

267
00:23:50,940 --> 00:23:52,510
Hurry and come.

268
00:23:52,550 --> 00:23:54,090
Let's go.

269
00:23:54,090 --> 00:23:55,880
One second.

270
00:23:58,790 --> 00:24:00,760
[Presidential Award]

271
00:24:08,240 --> 00:24:09,960
Let's go.

272
00:24:31,150 --> 00:24:33,460
Stand up straight. Move to the front if you're short.

273
00:24:33,460 --> 00:24:36,690
Stand to the side, and show your badge.

274
00:24:36,690 --> 00:24:38,090
Pose at an angle.

275
00:24:38,090 --> 00:24:40,130
Let's take a picture. Hurry.

276
00:24:40,130 --> 00:24:41,940
Come here.

277
00:24:41,940 --> 00:24:43,810
Can you pose?

278
00:24:43,810 --> 00:24:46,040
Just take the picture.

279
00:24:53,000 --> 00:24:55,610
Your dad is subhuman.

280
00:24:58,320 --> 00:25:02,660
You chose to be with her, knowing her dad was a monster.

281
00:25:02,660 --> 00:25:04,960
That's on you.

282
